TY  - JOUR
AU  - Hoberg, Gerard
AU  - Kumar, Nitin
AU  - Prabhala, Nagpurnanand
T1  - Buy-Side Competition and Momentum Profits
PY  - 2022
Y1  - 2022/01/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhab016
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 35
IS  - 1
SP  - 254
EP  - 298
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - We show that a new measure of buy-side competition explains momentum profits. The momentum quintile spread is 1.11% when competition is low and negligible when competition is high. Better alphas are attained with superior Sharpe and Sortino ratios, with no negative skewness, and in more investible strategies featuring value-weighted portfolios and large capitalization stocks. Stock characteristics traditionally related to momentum do not explain our results. Tests based on long-term reversals, the trading patterns of funds, their style peers, distant funds, and retail investors suggest that slow information diffusion explains the large momentum spreads and momentum reversals in low competition markets.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhab016
ER  - 



