TY  - JOUR
AU  - Hacamo, Isaac
AU  - Kleiner, Kristoph
T1  - Competing for Talent: Firms, Managers, and Social Networks
PY  - 2022
Y1  - 2022/01/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhab021
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 35
IS  - 1
SP  - 207
EP  - 253
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - Do social networks help firms recruit talented managers? In our setting, firms are randomly connected to prospective young managers through former employees. Under a discrete choice model, we find networks increase the likelihood firms hire high-ability managers, while having no effect on the hiring rate of low-ability managers. Effects are greatest for nonlocal firms, strong ties, and peers living in the same neighborhood. Survey evidence suggests social networks promote recruitment by providing information about firm fundamentals to potential applicants. Our results help rationalize why the majority of managers hold prior connections to the firm.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhab021
ER  - 



